Rating: 4
I made these, following the exact recipe, for a dinner party. I served them with whipped cream, raspberries & mint leaves. Everyone loved them. Next time, I would slightly decrease the baking time. 11 minutes made them just a little too done. I used the tart pans with removable bottoms. It was easy to pop them out of the pans, but not so easy to remove them from the bottom of the pan without deflating the cake, or turning them upside down. I used cooking spray on the pan, instead of butter. That might have been the difference. I would suggest serving them with ice cream, raspberries, raspberry sauce and mint.

Rating: 4
I never use the espresso powder. And i never bother to take the desert out of the ramekins. Serve with a good vanilla ice cream. I usually undercook so that they are still really molten in the middle.

Rating: 4
I made this for a Mexican dinner party for friends who aren't "dessert" people. Everyone raved about this. I made it in ramekins, served fresh out of the oven with vanilla bean ice cream. It probably could have been cooked a bit longer (I cooked it for 11 minutes as previously suggested) and I think next time I'll try it with bittersweet chocolate instead of semisweet.

